{"title":"Giant Trance & Liv Intrigue Advanced E+ Bring Full Power to Lightweight eMTBs","link":"https://bikerumor.com/giant-trance-liv-intrigue-advanced-e-bring-full-power-to-lightweight-emtbs/","date":1679998941000,"content":"<p>The lightweight e-bike trend usually comes with the compromise of lower power output, allowing the use of smaller motors and batteries to save weight. The new Giant Trance Advanced E+ Elite uses a new battery tech to deliver more power in a smaller package, allowing it to spec a full-power motor and let you choose when to let it rip.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-3-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"frame details on 2023 Giant Trance Advanced E+ Elite e-mountain bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-3-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-3-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-3-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-3-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-3-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-3.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new EnergyPak battery system uses higher-volume Panasonic cells to pack 400 Wh into a battery that weighs just 2.3 kg — about half the weight of typical e-bike batteries — and 4 kg (~9 pounds) lighter than Giant’s prior model.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Admittedly, the heavier cells usually have 500-600 Wh of power, but 400 Wh is still a lot more than the ~250 Wh usually found on lightweight eMTBs. So, these new Giant and Liv bikes strike a balance between the two and pair with an 85Nm Yamaha SyncDrive Pro motor.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-4-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"motor details on 2023 Giant Trance Advanced E+ Elite e-mountain bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-4-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-4-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-4-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-4-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-4-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-4.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The result is a bike that weighs as little as 18.8 kg (41 pounds) in size medium — also a middle ground between the ~32-pound ultralights and 55-pound big bikes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Giant says the larger battery cells make it more efficient and run cooler, but there’s no mention of a range extender external battery pack to boost playtime.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-2-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"frame details on 2023 Giant Trance Advanced E+ Elite e-mountain bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-2-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-2-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-2-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-2-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-2-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-2.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Able to provide up to 400% assist, the motor’s output is customizable with a companion app. Slide the torque adjuster up or down to match your needs and maximize output or range, or just try to match your buddy’s eMTB output so you can ride at the same level.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-5.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-5-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"frame details on 2023 Giant Trance Advanced E+ Elite e-mountain bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-5-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-5-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-5-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-5-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-5-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-5.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s not just the battery that’s saving weight. A full carbon frame with integrated one-piece 255g carbon bar-and-stem cockpits helps too, without giving up fit options.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The bar can adjust its mounting position to have an effective 40mm, 45mm, or 50mm stem length, and rotate the bar’s angle slightly too. Grips are size-specific as well, for an even more custom fit and feel.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-3-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"handlebar details \" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-3-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-3-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-3-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-3-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-3-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-3.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The bike has a one-button mode/power control built into the top tube display that shows the battery level and assist level. The tiny Ergo 3 handlebar remote gives you more control over modes, and you can add a second Ergo 3 controller on the other side to give you control over lights or use the Walk Assist mode.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-6-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"suspension details on 2023 Giant Trance Advanced E+ Elite e-mountain bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-6-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-6-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-6-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-6-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-6-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Giant-Trance-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-6.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The bike uses Giant’s Maestro suspension platform to deliver 140 mm of rear travel with a 27.5-inch rear wheel. Up front is a 150mm fork with a 29er wheel.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-2-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"closeup of suspension and motor on Liv Intrigue Advanced women's eMTB\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-2-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-2-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-2-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-2-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-2-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-2.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Top builds get Fox Live Valve suspension powered by the e-bike’s battery…and come in at $10k and $14k. A third model shares the same full carbon frame without Live Valve to hit $7,200, and a carbon front/alloy rear base model runs $6,000. Full specs for all <a href=\"https://www.giant-bicycles.com/us/trance-x-advanced-e-elite#element-30724\" target=\"_blank\">on Giant’s website</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Liv Intrigue Advanced E+ Elite Women’s eMTB</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-1-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"2023 liv intrigue advance e+ elite womens e-mountain bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-1-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-1-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-1-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-1-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Liv-Intrique-X-Advanced-eMTB-Elite-1.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Using all the same tech and features but in women’s builds and sizing, including travel, mixed wheel sizes, and geometry-adjusting flip chip, the Liv Intrigue Advanced E+ eMTB gets three of the same builds ranging from $6,000 to $10,000. Full specs and details <a href=\"https://www.liv-cycling.com/global/intrigue-x-advanced-e-elite\" target=\"_blank\">on its website</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/giant-trance-liv-intrigue-advanced-e-bring-full-power-to-lightweight-emtbs/\">Giant Trance &amp; Liv Intrigue Advanced E+ Bring Full Power to Lightweight eMTBs</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"7b53fed329d4c0249078afbb007ab77139097d4b6f1b51ef3d7cbab242dabd1e","category":"Cycling"}